Lizaad Williams (born 1 October 1993) is South African cricketer who plays for the Cape Cobras and Boland. Williams, who bowls right-arm fast was signed up with a rookie contract for the 2012/13 season after displays for Boland in List A cricket.

== Playing Style ==
Williams is a skiddy bowler with a front-on action and can bowl over 90 mph consistently. He has been touted by Ray Jennings as a "talent to watch out for". Williams is also a left-handed batsman who usually bats at number 10 or 11. He is never shy to have a word with the opposition and is known to be a colourful character on the field.

